-- HSBC Holdings May Walk Away From Plan to Buy Old Mutual's Nedbank, FT Says
-- B y   R e b e c c a   E v a n s   a n d   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2010-10-14T23:14:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/hsbc-holdings-may-walk-away-from-plan-to-buy-old-mutual-s-nedbank-ft-says.html
HSBC Holdings Pl c is close to
pulling out of a deal to acquire South Africa’s Nedbank, the
Financial Times reported, citing people close to the matter that
it didn’t identify.  HSBC spokesman  Adrian Russell  declined to comment on the
report by telephone.  To contact the editor responsible for this story: Ben Livesey at  blivesey@bloomberg.net  